    {
      "step_id": "quadrilateral_angle_sum",
      "sentences": [
        {
          "text": "Now, let's focus on the shape OQPR. It's a quadrilateral, and the sum of the interior angles of any quadrilateral is 360 degrees.",
          "khan_academy_text": "$\\text{In quadrilateral OQPR, sum of angles} = 360^{\\circ}$",
          "geometric_elements": [
            {
              "element_type": "region",
              "element_id": "region_quadrilateral_OQPR_interior",
              "animation_type": "highlight"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "So, we can write the equation: angle QOR plus angle ORP plus angle QPR plus angle OQP equals 360 degrees.",
          "khan_academy_text": "$\\angle QOR + \\angle ORP + \\angle QPR + \\angle OQP = 360^{\\circ}$",
          "geometric_elements": []
        },
        {
          "text": "Substituting 'a' and 'b' and our 90-degree angles, we get: b plus 90 degrees plus a plus 90 degrees equals 360 degrees.",
          "khan_academy_text": "$b + 90^{\\circ} + a + 90^{\\circ} = 360^{\\circ}$",
          "geometric_elements": []
        }
      ],
